\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\Sigma(\mathbf{k},i\omega_{n})=G_{0}(\mathbf{k,}i\omega_{n})^{-1}-G(\mathbf{k,}i\omega_{n})^{-1}
\]

\end_inset

On a alors 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
G(\mathbf{k,}i\omega_{n})=\frac{1}{i\omega_{n}+\mu-\varepsilon_{\mathbf{k}}-\Sigma(\mathbf{k},i\omega_{n})}
\]

\end_inset

On définit alors la fonction de Green locale (dans toute la suite, on omettra
